<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-3548] Locale is not handled properly in kafka-consumer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3548</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the JVM local language is Turkish, which has different upper case for the lower case letter i, the result is a runtime error caused by org.apache.kafka.clients.consumer.OffsetResetStrategy. More specifically an enum constant &lt;b&gt;EARL&#304;EST&lt;/b&gt; is generated which does not match &lt;b&gt;EARLIEST&lt;/b&gt; (note the &lt;em&gt;dotted capital i&lt;/em&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the locale for the JVM is explicitly set to en_US, the example runs as expected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A sample error log is below:&lt;/p&gt;
